concept_explanation.request_body_response_entity:
**@RequestBody and ResponseEntity:**

```java
// @RequestBody — deserialize JSON request body to Java object:
@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity<Product> create(@RequestBody Product product) {
    // HTTP body: {"name":"Mouse","price":799}
    // Spring uses Jackson to deserialize → Product object
    Product saved = service.save(product);
    return ResponseEntity
        .status(HttpStatus.CREATED)  // 201
        .body(saved);
}

// @PutMapping — update:
@PutMapping("/{id}")
public ResponseEntity<Product> update(@PathVariable String id,
                                       @RequestBody Product product) {
    return service.update(id, product)
        .map(ResponseEntity::ok)                      // 200 with updated product
        .orElse(ResponseEntity.notFound().build());   // 404 if not found
}

// @DeleteMapping — no response body:
@DeleteMapping("/{id}")
public ResponseEntity<Void> delete(@PathVariable String id) {
    if (service.delete(id)) {
        return ResponseEntity.noContent().build();    // 204 No Content
    }
    return ResponseEntity.notFound().build();         // 404
}

// Convenience shortcuts:
ResponseEntity.ok(body)              // 200 + body
ResponseEntity.created(uri).body(b) // 201 + Location header
ResponseEntity.noContent().build()  // 204, no body
ResponseEntity.notFound().build()   // 404, no body
ResponseEntity.badRequest().body(e) // 400 + error
```

concept_explanation.http_status_codes:
**HTTP status codes — use the right one:**

```
2xx Success:
  200 OK            — GET (found), PUT (updated), PATCH
  201 Created       — POST (created new resource)
  204 No Content    — DELETE (success, nothing to return)

4xx Client Error:
  400 Bad Request   — invalid request body, validation failure
  401 Unauthorized  — not logged in
  403 Forbidden     — logged in but no permission
  404 Not Found     — resource doesn't exist
  409 Conflict      — duplicate (e.g., duplicate username)

5xx Server Error:
  500 Internal Server Error — unexpected exception
```

```java
// WRONG — returning 200 for resource not found:
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public Product get(@PathVariable String id) {
    return service.findById(id).orElse(null);  // null → empty 200 response!
}

// RIGHT — 404 when not found:
@GetMapping("/{id}")
public ResponseEntity<Product> get(@PathVariable String id) {
    return service.findById(id)
        .map(ResponseEntity::ok)
        .orElse(ResponseEntity.notFound().build()); // 404
}
```

concept_explanation.request_response_records:
**Request and response record design:**

```java
// Use separate request/response records — not your domain entity directly:

// Domain entity (internal):
public class Product {
    private String id;  // generated by server
    private String name;
    private double price;
    private String createdAt;  // server-set timestamp
}

// Request record — what the client sends (no id, no createdAt):
public record ProductRequest(String name, double price) {}

// Response record — what the server returns (includes id, createdAt):
public record ProductResponse(String id, String name, double price, String createdAt) {}

// Controller uses both:
@PostMapping
public ResponseEntity<ProductResponse> create(@RequestBody ProductRequest req) {
    Product saved = service.create(req.name(), req.price());
    return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED)
        .body(toResponse(saved));
}
```

This separation prevents over-posting (clients can't set id or createdAt) and lets you evolve the internal model independently of the API contract.

step_by_step_solution.details:
```java
// Domain entity (internal service layer):
public record Product(String id, String name, String category, double price) {}

// Request — what the client sends (no id — server generates it):
public record ProductRequest(String name, String category, double price) {}
```

```java
@Service
public class ProductService {
    private final Map<String, Product> store = new LinkedHashMap<>();
    private int seq = 1;

    public List<Product> findAll()                      { return new ArrayList<>(store.values()); }
    public List<Product> findByCategory(String cat)     {
        return store.values().stream()
            .filter(p -> p.category().equalsIgnoreCase(cat)).toList();
    }
    public Optional<Product> findById(String id)        { return Optional.ofNullable(store.get(id)); }
    public Product save(ProductRequest req) {
        String id = "P" + String.format("%03d", seq++);
        Product p = new Product(id, req.name(), req.category(), req.price());
        store.put(id, p); return p;
    }
    public Optional<Product> update(String id, ProductRequest req) {
        if (!store.containsKey(id)) return Optional.empty();
        Product p = new Product(id, req.name(), req.category(), req.price());
        store.put(id, p); return Optional.of(p);
    }
    public boolean delete(String id) {
        return store.remove(id) != null;
    }
}
```

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/products")
public class ProductController {
    private final ProductService service;
    ProductController(ProductService service) { this.service = service; }

    // GET /api/products OR GET /api/products?category=Electronics
    @GetMapping
    public List<Product> getAll(
            @RequestParam(required = false) String category) {
        return category != null ? service.findByCategory(category)
                                : service.findAll();
    }

    // GET /api/products/P001 → 200 or 404
    @GetMapping("/{id}")
    public ResponseEntity<Product> getById(@PathVariable String id) {
        return service.findById(id)
            .map(ResponseEntity::ok)
            .orElse(ResponseEntity.notFound().build());
    }

    // POST /api/products → 201
    @PostMapping
    public ResponseEntity<Product> create(@RequestBody ProductRequest req) {
        Product saved = service.save(req);
        return ResponseEntity.status(HttpStatus.CREATED).body(saved);
    }

    // PUT /api/products/P001 → 200 or 404
    @PutMapping("/{id}")
    public ResponseEntity<Product> update(@PathVariable String id,
                                           @RequestBody ProductRequest req) {
        return service.update(id, req)
            .map(ResponseEntity::ok)
            .orElse(ResponseEntity.notFound().build());
    }

    // DELETE /api/products/P001 → 204 or 404
    @DeleteMapping("/{id}")
    public ResponseEntity<Void> delete(@PathVariable String id) {
        return service.delete(id)
            ? ResponseEntity.noContent().build()       // 204
            : ResponseEntity.notFound().build();       // 404
    }
}
```

